column1: # selection down to apparent mag 14.0. ONLY STARS WITH FLAG DUPLICATED_SOURCE SET TO FALSE were retained.
# This is the result of TWO queries made directly on the gaia website. There are 2 main steps involved in the selection
# 1) select stars within 250 pc (parallax > 4 mas) AND apparent mag <=14 AND absolute mag between 3 and 8.
#    This ensure only solar type stars are retained (precisely from F0V to K7V).
# 2) use the output of this first query (splitted into 4 tables to speed operations up) to select  double stars.
#    A pais of stars is considered to be a candidate double if:
#    c) Difference on proper motion along the RA direction < 2 km/s
#    d) Difference on proper motion along the DEC direction < 2 km/s

column2: distance accuracy (better than 2 pc) and luminosity.

column1: #   At this stage proper motion is converted into velocity in km/s converting mas/yr
#   and parallax in mas into the corresponding unit as follow:
#   V km/s = 3.08e13/206265/(365.25*24*3600)* (PM mas/yr) / (parallax in mas) = 4.7317 pm/parallax
#   Error on proper motion is calculated as follow (adding in quadrature the effect due to proper motion and parallax errors):
#   All quantities are rounded down to a sensible number of decimal digits (GAIA archive do not round numbers).
#    'false' = duplicated_source                                               <=== this is new compared with previous selections
# to create 4 small tables for quick further analysis
# select * from user_rscarpa.bestCandidates_m8_3_m13_d4 as t where t.ra<180 and t.dec > 0
# select * from user_rscarpa.bestCandidates_m8_3_m13_d4 as t where t.ra<180 and t.dec <= 0
# select * from user_rscarpa.bestCandidates_m8_3_m13_d4 as t where t.ra>=180 and t.dec > 0
# select * from user_rscarpa.bestCandidates_m8_3_m13_d4 as t where t.ra>=180 and t.dec <= 0
#  Second SQL query to find double candidates.
#  Each of the above 4 tables is used as input for the following query to find double stars.
#  Looks for stars with another star within projected distance of 2pc

column2: and proper motion difference of 4 km in both ra and dec.
